<entry>
<author><name><![CDATA[Jcee]]></name></author>
<updated>2015-12-20T17:55:14-07:00</updated>
<published>2015-12-20T17:55:14-07:00</published>
<id>http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=5502&amp;p=24126#p24126</id>
<link href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=5502&amp;p=24126#p24126"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: Windows 10 start menu custom background picture]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=5502&amp;p=24126#p24126"><![CDATA[
It sounds like blur isnt working on your system for whatever reason: you can remove transparency completely from the image<br /><br />alternatively you can mess around with this line of code at the end of resource 1 (be sure to compile afterwards)<br />Main_opacity=Region<br />This will override the default setting (fullglass), and the option 'increase transparency' as it is defined later in the file.<br /><br />also you may look into also setting to Region:<br />Main_opacity2=<br />Submenu_opacity=<br /><br /><span style="font-family:Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"><strong><span style="background-color:#e6f2fa;">Main_opacity</span></strong></span><span style="font-family:Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="background-color:#e6f2fa;"> can be </span></span><span style="font-family:Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"><strong><span style="background-color:#e6f2fa;">solid</span></strong></span><span style="font-family:Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="background-color:#e6f2fa;">, </span></span><span style="font-family:Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"><strong><span style="background-color:#e6f2fa;">region</span></strong></span><span style="font-family:Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="background-color:#e6f2fa;">, </span></span><span style="font-family:Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"><strong><span style="background-color:#e6f2fa;">alpha</span></strong></span><span style="font-family:Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="background-color:#e6f2fa;">, </span></span><span style="font-family:Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"><strong><span style="background-color:#e6f2fa;">glass, fullalpha </span></strong></span><span style="font-family:Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="background-color:#e6f2fa;">or</span></span><span style="font-family:Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"><strong><span style="background-color:#e6f2fa;"> fullglass</span></strong></span><span style="font-family:Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="background-color:#e6f2fa;">. </span></span><span style="font-family:Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"><strong><span style="background-color:#e6f2fa;">Solid</span></strong></span><span style="font-family:Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="background-color:#e6f2fa;"> means the menu will be filled with the </span></span><span style="font-family:Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"><strong><span style="background-color:#e6f2fa;">Main_background</span></strong></span><span style="font-family:Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="background-color:#e6f2fa;"> color and the bitmap will be drawn on top. </span></span><span style="font-family:Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"><strong><span style="background-color:#e6f2fa;">Region</span></strong></span><span style="font-family:Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="background-color:#e6f2fa;"> means the pixels with alpha=0 will be transparent, and the rest will be opaque. </span></span><span style="font-family:Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"><strong><span style="background-color:#e6f2fa;">Alpha</span></strong></span><span style="font-family:Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="background-color:#e6f2fa;"> means that the bitmap will be alpha-blended with the desktop behind it. </span></span><span style="font-family:Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"><strong><span style="background-color:#e6f2fa;">Glass</span></strong></span><span style="font-family:Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="background-color:#e6f2fa;"> means the pixels with alpha=0 will be transparent, all the rest will blend between the glass color and the pixel color &#40;alpha=1 is full glass, alpha=255 is fully opaque&#41;. </span></span><span style="font-family:Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"><strong><span style="background-color:#e6f2fa;">Fullalpha</span></strong></span><span style="font-family:Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="background-color:#e6f2fa;"> and </span></span><span style="font-family:Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"><strong><span style="background-color:#e6f2fa;">fullglass</span></strong></span><span style="font-family:Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="background-color:#e6f2fa;"> are the same as alpha/glass but inform the start menu that the background behind the menu items can be transparent.</span></span><br /><br />The blue text is ripped from the help webpage: <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/tutorials/skintutorial.html" class="postlink">http://www.classicshell.net/tutorials/skintutorial.html</a> so a quick ctrl+f will help you find that section<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=62">Jcee</a> — Sun Dec 20, 2015 5:55 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
</entry>
